 from animal skin. Since it was against their religious belief so they were resisted it which led to a skirmish between the traders and British soldiers. After this event the fight for freedom gained the impetus which it lacked before. In the following years many prominent leaders emerged and led this movement for freedom. Like other revolutions, India’s revolution was also marked with some extremely gory events in which many people sacrificed their lives for this cause. On the other end of the spectrum there were legends like Mahatma Gandhi who believed in the concept of non-violence and fought this was with unwavering faith in this concept. Finally on 15 August 1947 British agreed to relinquish control over India. Now I want to write about all these incidents and put them in the contemporary context so that I can make our youngsters realize that the free air we are breathing today came at a hefty cost and now we have a responsibility to do justice to the sacrifices made and take this country towards the destiny which our freedom fighters had envisaged.', 'word_count': 503, 'sentence_count': 22, 'fc': 6.0, 'lr': 6.0, 'gra': 5.0, 'p': 6.0, 'strict_overall': 5.0, 'strict_reason': '(truncated)', 'scoring_method': 'official_rubric_llm_judge', 'source_url': 'https://practicepteonline.com/ielts-speaking-cue-card-a-book-you-want-to-write/'}

